===Verb===
{{en-verb|buys|buying|bought|'''[[bought]]''' ''or'' {{qualifier|rare|dialectal}} '''[[boughten]]''' }}

# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To [[obtain]] (something) in [[exchange]] for money or goods
#: {{usex|I'm going to '''buy''' my father something nice for his birthday.|lang=en}}
#* Benjamin Franklin
#*: '''Buy''' what thou hast no need of, and ere long thou wilt sell thy necessaries.
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To obtain by some sacrifice.
#: {{usex|I've '''bought''' material comfort by foregoing my dreams.|lang=en}}
#* Bible, Proverbs xxiii. 23
#*: '''Buy''' the truth and sell it not; also wisdom, and instruction, and understanding.
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To [[bribe]].
#: {{usex|He tried to '''buy''' me with gifts, but I wouldn't give up my beliefs.|lang=en}}
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To be equivalent to in value.
#: {{usex|The dollar doesn't '''buy''' as much as it used to.'|lang=en}}
# {{context|transitive|informal|lang=en}} to [[accept]] as true; to [[believe]]
#: {{usex|I'm not going to '''buy''' your stupid excuses anymore!|lang=en}}
# {{context|intransitive|lang=en}} To make a purchase or purchases, to [[treat]] (for a meal)
#: {{usex|She '''buys''' for Federated.|lang=en}}
#: {{usex|Let's go out for dinner. I'm '''buying'''.|lang=en}}
# {{context|poker slang|transitive|lang=en}} To make a [[bluff]], usually a large one.
#: {{usex|Smith tried to '''buy''' the pot on the river with a huge bluff|lang=en}}

